Elections can only be credible if they involve all members of society, including women, the UN representative in Afghanistan said on Wednesday.
Nicholas Haysom, the head of the UN relief mission, said that local elections are contested by hundreds of women, three women are running for vice president, and more than 30 percent of the newly registered voters are women.
"The role of women cannot be overlooked", he said in his statement on Wednesday.
